  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women&#x2019;s capacity building on hygiene and livelihood creation through production of sanitary napkins</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a unique initiative where STARS organisation is going to organise women in preparing &#x2018;sanitary napkins&#x2019;. The idea is to produce napkins at marketable level and create livelihood opportunities for rural women.  First year of the project will consist of following activities: - 
Settle initial logistics like putting the team in place and initial orientation. 
Reach out to important stakeholders, viz. village women, local authorities, traditional and religious leaders.  
Establish necessary structures like project implementation committee with men and women.
Discuss components of the project like discussion on hygiene/sanitary napkin through REFLECT, establishing co-operative, develop manuals for women. Conduct training for the community leaders through mullah. Training women for producing napkins with cloths and cottons.
Supervision, monitoring, follow up and regular reporting.
Prepare a professional proposal for future resource generation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is going to create a group of self-employed women who will pave the ways of affordable and locally appropriate sanitary napkins. Pushing the social and traditional boundaries these women will create a system of producing affordable sanitary pad in hope of starting a hygiene movement.
Sanitary napkin is universally needed product. Yet has very low presence in rural Afghanistan, partly due to its high price/ inaccessibility and partly due to the tradition of using cheaper alternatives. They therefore become the host of many infectious diseases. This is due to lack of awareness and economic inability for adopting better precautions like use of good sanitary napkins during menstruation period.  This initiative will &#x2013; 1) create hygiene awareness through REFLECT, 2) provide livelihood opportunities for women, 3) organise women groups towards formation of co-operative societies, 4) involve Govt. authorities, religious leaders, village elders and Shura members in this initiative.</narrative>
  </description>
